    <h2 style="text-align: center;">February 2018: VIX blows and new positions</h2>

<p style="margin: 10px 0;padding: 0;mso-line-height-rule: exactly;-ms-text-size-adjust: 100%;-webkit-text-size-adjust: 100%;color: #202020;font-family: Helvetica;font-size: 16px;line-height: 150%;text-align: left;"> <br>
    Dear investors,<br>
    <br>
    The fund returned +3.5% net of fees and costs in February. The S&P500 lost -3.9% and the ASX200 returned -2.1%. This was largely due to our hedging overlay.<br>
    <br>
    <img data-file-id="2858969" height="139" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/08c26e5e46cf7c109889f7d9d/images/c61cf2c0-4966-49e0-a63e-4917e4e36433.png" style="border: 0px;width: 600px;height: 139px;margin: 0px;outline: none;text-decoration: none;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" width="600"><br>
    <br>
    In January markets were up, but we made money selling them short. In February, markets were down, but our most profitable long was buying the Nasdaq.<br>
    <br>
    Our overlay strategy has now grossed over 10% for the fund since inception. We invested the proceeds in Facebook, Google and Samsung, so the true returns from the early Feb volatility blow-out will include the profits from those.<br>
    <br>
    So not only were investors <em>up</em> when the market was <em>down</em>, but investor ownership of our portfolio companies increased by around 10%. <br>
    <br>
    <img data-file-id="2859093" height="351" src="https://gallery.mailchimp.com/08c26e5e46cf7c109889f7d9d/images/d55c1e44-9629-466d-8119-c90868df9ddc.png" style="border: 0px;width: 600px;height: 351px;margin: 0px;outline: none;text-decoration: none;-ms-interpolation-mode: bicubic;" width="600"><br>
